data.customers_say: Customers find these dog toys cute and fun to play with, keeping their pets entertained for quite some time. They appreciate the lack of stuffing and consider them good value for money. The durability receives mixed feedback - while some say they last a long time, others report they shred in less than 10 minutes. The squeaking feature also gets mixed reviews, with some loving the crinkle noise while others report quick destruction of the squeakers. While some customers say they're good for aggressive chewers, others note they're not suitable for strong chewers.

top_reviews.review_title: Perfect Combo of Fun, Durability, and Value
top_reviews.review_comment: I couldn't be happier with this 5-pack bundle of plush dog squeaky toys! This is a repeat purchase. Right out of the box, our BFFs were so excited and immediately grabbed one to run around with. Each toy in the assortment is a nice size – perfect for any size dogs who love to chew, toss, and squeak their toys to their heart’s content. The variety is great, keeping playtime fresh and fun. Multiple squeakers, which really keeps our dogs engaged. The material is soft but surprisingly durable – we’ve had them for a couple of weeks now, and not a single tear, which is impressive considering my dog usually destroys toys within days. This bundle offers excellent value for the price – five quality toys in one pack! It's also a great option if you’re looking to stock up on gifts for your dog or even for a dog-loving friend. I’ll definitely be buying another set when we need replacements. Highly recommend!
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: I absolutely love these. They are long enough that I can use for training puppy while not getting bit. My puppy loves them. She has not torn any apart and she is a lab. Also there is a squeaker on both ends. They are so soft and durable. They have been chewed on for over a month and no tears so far.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2025

top_reviews.review_title: Just what I was looking for and last a bit longer than expected
top_reviews.review_comment: Pretty good value as far as pet toys go. My GSD mauls 'em hard so each one might last a week. But there's five, so she's covered. The squeaky balls inside get punctured fast, but c'est la vie.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on July 16, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: takes our mini weiner a good few days to break through to the squeaker of the toy- i love that they don’t have stuffing so i don’t have to worry about him eating that but i do have to keep an eye out once he starts ripping it enough to get to the plastic squeaker or else he will ingest it like the little puppy idiot he is (: Overall i LOVE that it comes with multiple so that i have backups without spending a ton of money weekly
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2024

top_reviews.review_title: Puppy loves them! And no stuffing everywhere!
top_reviews.review_comment: My dog loves these - as an aggressive chewer, stuffing is not good for us. She hasn't torn any of these apart yet, which is shocking, not has she killed any of the squeakers. She loves them. Tossing them around and has a hard time choosing which one she wants to play with.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2025

top_reviews.review_title: It's a good deal, but not for serious dog play
top_reviews.review_comment: I opened the box last night and let my two dogs have at 'em. Within an hour, the squeakers on two of the toys no longer worked, and shortly after that, one of the toys looked like roadkill that had been hit by a semi with its guts hanging out. In the seller's defense, they offer this 'tip': "Please kindly note these toys are not for extra aggressive chewers, such as hound." However, my 10-year-old lab and small mutt aren't what I would call "aggressive chewers," but the toys didn't stand up to their brief session of tug-of-war. The dogs had fun, but the toys only lasted a couple of days.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: So, my girl Border Collies love to tug but won't pull on tug ropes. One of them will de-gut a fluff filled toy in short order, so we get these for them. They aren't made for being a tug toy, but they hold up pretty well. We know that they are going to be ripped apart, but at least there is no stuffing to pick up. The squeakers are sewn into a fabric pouch, so they are easy to pick up--no plastic parts chewed up.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: My dog loves the unstuffy, she really makes them squeak! She loves to shake them fiercely and no fear of stuffing flying out. They are also really cute and good value for the price of all 5.
